body:
## 🐛 Bug Report

I'd like to fit image to single cell with margin.
But addImage({ row: 1.1 to 1.9, col: 1.1 to 1.9 }) is not expected image size.

Lib version: 4.2.1

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
const wb = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
const ws = wb.addWorksheet('sheet1');

const res = await fetch('https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/401369');
const imgBuffer = await res.arrayBuffer();

ws.getColumn(1).width = 3;
ws.getColumn(2).width = 20;
ws.getColumn(3).width = 3;

ws.getRow(1).height = 10;
ws.getRow(2).height = 100;
ws.getRow(3).height = 10;
ws.getRow(4).height = 100;
ws.getRow(5).height = 10;
ws.getRow(6).height = 100;
ws.getRow(7).height = 10;

const imageId = wb.addImage({
buffer: imgBuffer,
  extension: 'png',
});

ws.addImage(imageId, {
  tl: { col: 1, row: 1 },
  br: { col: 2, row: 2 }
});

ws.addImage(imageId, {
  tl: { col: 1.1, row: 3.1 },
  br: { col: 1.9, row: 3.9 }
});

ws.addImage(imageId, {
  tl: { col: 1.1, row: 5.1 },
  br: { col: 2.9, row: 6.9 }
});
```

[Full repro code is here!](https://jsfiddle.net/amay077/01bv5mo4)

First and third images are expected, but second image is unexpected.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/401369/111771986-ae6ef280-88ef-11eb-9e26-f9cd6777adec.png)

## The expected behaviour:

The expected second image is 10% margin.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/401369/111772108-d4949280-88ef-11eb-880c-273149e9c07a.png)


## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

I'm not sure.
Any solution?

